---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Child Custody Modification Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  description="Need to modify a Maryland child custody order? Our attorneys handle custody modification cases when circumstances have materially changed. Rockville & Baltimore offices."
  ogTitle="Child Custody Modification Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  ogDescription="Maryland child custody modification attorneys. When life changes, your custody order can too. Free consultation with our Rockville and Baltimore family law team."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-slate-700 text-white py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Maryland Custody Modification Attorneys</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
        Life Changes. Your Custody<br class="hidden md:block" />
        Order Can Too.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        When significant changes in your life or your child's circumstances make the existing custody arrangement unworkable or harmful, Maryland law allows you to seek a modification. Our attorneys know how to build the legal case for change.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Schedule Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white hover:bg-white hover:text-slate-900 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Call (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Legal Standard -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-5">The Legal Standard for Custody Modification</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Maryland courts start with a strong presumption in favor of maintaining the existing custody order. To successfully modify custody, you must generally demonstrate two things:
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-4">
            <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">1. Material Change in Circumstances</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A significant change that wasn't anticipated when the original order was entered and that affects the welfare of the child.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">2. Modification Is in the Child's Best Interests</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Even after a material change is shown, the court must find that changing custody actually serves the child's best interests.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            The threshold required — and how courts apply it — can vary based on the nature of the change and the type of modification sought. Our attorneys help you evaluate whether your situation meets the legal standard and build the strongest possible case.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Common Grounds for Modification</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              "A parent's relocation to a different city or state",
              "Significant change in a parent's work schedule",
              "Remarriage or new partner in the home",
              "A parent's new substance abuse problem or criminal activity",
              "Child's changing needs as they grow older",
              "Evidence of domestic violence or child abuse",
              "One parent consistently violating the existing order",
              "The child's expressed preference (at an appropriate age)",
              "A parent's serious illness or disability",
              "Change in the child's school or educational needs"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-500 font-bold mt-0.5">✓</span>
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Types of Modifications -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Types of Custody Modifications</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Custody modifications range from minor scheduling adjustments to complete reversals of the existing custody arrangement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: "Parenting Schedule Modification",
            desc: "Adjusting holiday schedules, vacation time, pickup/dropoff arrangements, or day-to-day time-sharing without changing the underlying custody designation.",
            scope: "Minor to Moderate"
          },
          {
            title: "Physical Custody Modification",
            desc: "Changing where the child primarily resides — for example, shifting from sole physical custody with one parent to shared physical custody, or vice versa.",
            scope: "Significant"
          },
          {
            title: "Legal Custody Modification",
            desc: "Changing who has decision-making authority — for example, shifting from shared legal custody to sole legal custody when co-parenting communication has completely broken down.",
            scope: "Significant"
          }
        ].map(type => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 bg-amber-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Scope: {type.scope}</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-3">{type.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">{type.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Relocation Focus -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-5">Relocation: One of the Most Complex Modifications</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            When one parent wants to move a significant distance away — especially out of state — the impact on the existing custody arrangement can be profound. These cases are among the most contested in Maryland family law.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Courts carefully evaluate the reason for the relocation, the impact on the child's relationship with the remaining parent, and whether a new custody/visitation arrangement can adequately preserve both relationships.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            We represent parents on both sides: those seeking to relocate with their children, and those trying to prevent the other parent from taking their children away.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">What Courts Consider in Relocation Cases</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "The reason for the move (job, family support, new spouse)",
              "The impact on the child's stability and continuity",
              "The quality of the child's relationship with each parent",
              "The relocating parent's willingness to facilitate the other parent's relationship",
              "Whether the remaining parent would also relocate",
              "The child's ties to current community, school, and friends",
              "The child's age and adaptability"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-500 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Emergency Modifications -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-red-50 border-y border-red-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Emergency Custody Modifications</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">When your child's safety is at immediate risk, Maryland courts can grant emergency custody modifications — sometimes within 24 hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">When Emergency Action May Be Required</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "Immediate risk of abuse or neglect",
              "Parent is actively using drugs or alcohol around the child",
              "Imminent risk of parental abduction",
              "Child is being exposed to domestic violence",
              "Parent is threatening to take child out of state or country",
              "Sudden abandonment of care responsibilities"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-red-500 font-bold mt-0.5">⚠</span>
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Our Emergency Response</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">
            When a child's safety is at risk, there is no time to wait. Our attorneys are experienced in obtaining emergency protective orders and expedited custody hearings in Maryland courts.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">
            We move quickly to file the necessary motions, present compelling evidence to the court, and obtain relief that protects your child immediately.
          </p>
          <a href="tel:2402693592" class="block text-center bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
            Call Now: (240) 269-3592
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Modification Process -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">The Custody Modification Process in Maryland</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        {[
          { step: "01", title: "Free Consultation", desc: "We evaluate your situation and assess whether your circumstances meet the legal standard for modification." },
          { step: "02", title: "File Motion", desc: "We draft and file a Motion to Modify Custody with the appropriate Maryland Circuit Court." },
          { step: "03", title: "Hearing & Evidence", desc: "We present your case to the judge with documentary evidence, witness testimony, and legal argument." },
          { step: "04", title: "New Order Issued", desc: "The court issues a modified custody order that reflects the new arrangement." }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-amber-500 text-white text-xl font-bold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">{item.step}</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-amber-500">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Your Child's Needs Have Changed. Your Custody Order Can Too.</h2>
      <p class="text-amber-100 mb-8 text-lg">Talk to our Maryland custody modification attorneys for a free evaluation of your case.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-white text-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-50 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-amber-600 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
